Miller Family user stories:
As a married user, I want to be able to share accounts with my partner for a full scope of family finances.
As a user dealing with many small purchases I want to be able to tag my purchases, so I can separate subscriptions and ongoing payments with an end date from general categories. 
As a user that likes visualization, I want to be able to have clear and well thought out visualizations for my budgeting.

User Scenario:
Jill logs into MapMyMint after finishing the week’s grocery shopping and paying a few school and sports fees for her children. With a busy household of six, she wants to quickly check how the family budget is doing.
When she opens the dashboard, she sees clear visual charts showing spending on groceries, utilities, school costs, and other household expenses. She notices that several small convenience purchases and a couple of subscriptions have added up more than expected this month.
Jill reviews the categories and tags a few recurring subscriptions so they are easier to track. The dashboard updates and shows how the current spending affects the family’s savings goal for their future move.
Before closing the app, Jill shares the updated budget summary with Jack so he can review it later. The clear visual overview helps Jill quickly understand the family’s finances and keep the household budget on track.

Requirements Specification:
The system shall allow Jill to track all high-volume household expenses, automatically categorizing them and updating budget totals in real time. 
At any time, it shall highlight unusual or unnecessary spending, including small fragmented purchases and recurring subscriptions, using clear visual indicators. 
The app shall provide easy-to-view metrics to show spending trends, budget status, and alerts for approaching limits. 
Jill shall be able to securely share the budget with Jack or export summaries, and create future savings goals with simulations showing the impact of spending adjustments. 
Upon login, the system shall display a dashboard of key financial metrics for fast, informed decision-making.
